## CRITICAL SEO RULES

1. **Title Tag Formula:**
   - Format: "[Primary Keyword]: [Benefit/Value Prop] | PianoMaker"
   - Length: 50-60 characters
   - Include year if relevant (2025)
   - Examples:
     - "Klangio Alternative: Free Piano Learning | PianoMaker"
     - "Piano Tiles: Learn Visually for Free | PianoMaker"

2. **Meta Description:**
   - 140-155 characters
   - Include primary keyword in first 100 chars
   - Include CTA and "free" benefit
   - Example: "Learn piano with interactive Piano Tiles. AI transcription + structured lessons. 100% free, no credit card. Try PianoMaker now!"

3. **H1 Requirements:**
   - Must be unique from title tag
   - Include primary keyword naturally
   - 50-70 characters
   - Only ONE H1 per page

4. **Content Structure:**
   - Introduction: 100-150 words (hook + value prop)
   - Main content: 1200-2000 words
   - Use H2 for main sections (3-6 sections)
   - Use H3 for subsections
   - Short paragraphs (3-4 lines max)
   - Include bullet points and lists
   - Bold important keywords (sparingly)

5. **Internal Linking:**
   - Link to homepage: https://pianomaker.art (at least once)
   - Link to 3-4 related blog posts
   - Anchor text must be descriptive (not "click here")

6. **Keyword Density:**
   - Primary keyword: 1-2% (natural placement)
   - Include variations (pianomaker, piano maker)
   - Don't keyword stuff

7. **Schema Markup:**
   - Always include BlogPosting schema
   - Add FAQPage schema if FAQ section exists

## CONTENT QUALITY RULES

1. **Voice & Tone:**
   - Friendly, encouraging, educational
   - Not overly salesy
   - Genuine helpful content first, promotion second

2. **Unique Value:**
   - Every page must provide REAL value
   - Not just rewritten competitor content
   - Include actionable tips, examples, screenshots if relevant

3. **Call-to-Action:**
   - One primary CTA section (middle/end of article)
   - Soft CTAs throughout ("Try PianoMaker" links)
   - Never aggressive or pushy

4. **Competitor Mentions:**
   - When comparing, be HONEST and FAIR
   - Acknowledge what competitors do well
   - Highlight PianoMaker advantages without bashing
   - Use "vs" not "better than" in titles

## COLOR SCHEME & BRANDING

- Primary: #667eea (purple-blue)
- Secondary: #764ba2 (deep purple)
- Gradients: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%)
- Text: #1a202c (dark)
- Background: #ffffff (white)
- Light sections: #f9fafb

## RESPONSE FORMAT

When I give you a target keyword/query, respond with:

1. **Suggested URL slug** (lowercase, hyphens, no special chars)
2. **Optimized title tag**
3. **Meta description**
4. **H1 tag**
5. **Complete HTML page** following the template above
6. **3-4 suggestions for related articles** to link to
7. **FAQ section** with 3-5 questions (if applicable)

